page.title: 09R.A.F.Wethersfield - People
page.content: There are mainly American people on the base, there are both men and women, and everyone has to work. There is a kindergarten that the young children go to, then they go to a lower school. On average there are roughly 200 children at this school. After lower school they go to high school in Lakenheath. As they have no half terms they have a very long summer holiday and as it's an American school they have American holidays. The unmarried people live in barracks and the married live in semi-detached houses or terraces.
